1
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:41,520
I remember

2
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:44,080
there's a poem

3
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,200
you used to recite.

4
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,640
The clouds and moon in it

5
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:55,600
must be talking

6
00:01:58,759 --> 00:02:01,800
about the two of us.

7
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,360
Please come in.

8
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:49,880
This house is quite elegant.

9
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,120
Ruisheng,

10
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:53,360
but I heard Tian Jiatai died in here.

11
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,160
Aren't you superstitious?

12
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:56,420
After Mr. Hechen left,

13
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:59,079
this place became confiscated property.

14
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:01,120
Thanks to Minister Zhou's care for me.

15
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,880
I thought about missing my homeland and old friends,

16
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,640
so keeping it has its benefits.

17
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,640
Changgeng,

18
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:08,960
our first meeting

19
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,160
was also here, right?

20
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,900
Mr. Hechen treated us.

21
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,120
At that time, my Chanel

22
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,450
was lost for three days.

23
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,000
You went through so much trouble

24
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,240
to find her for me.

25
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,400
Chanel is still in my lower courtyard now.

26
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,660
If she gets lost again,

27
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,600
I'll have to rely on you, Changgeng.

28
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,460
Don't say that.

29
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,610
Mr. Jin, you are different now.

30
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,570
How could you possibly need me?

31
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,579
But if you need anything, Mr. Jin,

32
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,280
I'm willing to serve you with utmost loyalty.

33
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,280
Okay?

34
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,920
Right, I heard

35
00:03:36,160 --> 00:03:39,240
Minister Zhou is setting up a company now

36
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,320
to underwrite salt.

37
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,410
But as far as I know, Mrs. He.

38
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,640
The most profitable salt and opium in Shanghai

39
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,520
are all controlled by the Japanese.

40
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,880
How is his business going?

41
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,360
The salt in Jiangsu and Zhejiang provinces

42
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,290
is now in the hands of the Japanese.

43
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,960
Minister Zhou also wants to get the trading rights back,

44
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,200
but how could the Japanese let go?

45
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,380
Come on, everyone.

46
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,480
This way, please.

47
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,080
Changgeng, take the seat of honor.

48
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:05,840
Okay.

49
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,160
Mr. He, here.

50
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,160
Come.

51
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,800
Two Madams, please sit.

52
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,720
Let's continue.

53
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:18,959
In other places,

54
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:21,519
traffic is inconvenient, wars are endless,

55
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:23,000
and purchasing power is poor.

56
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,480
Small-scale smuggling is okay.

57
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,280
If we want to set up a company,

58
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,880
it's a thankless task.

59
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,600
So it hasn't progressed at all.

60
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,560
So, Mr. Jin.

61
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:38,280
I actually came today to present you a treasure.

62
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,080
Mr. He,

63
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:43,159
Mr. He is the treasure I'm talking about.

64
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,840
Does Mr. He have any good ideas?

65
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,120
Deputy Chief Jin,

66
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:54,560
do you know what goods are the most valuable in the market

67
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:56,920
besides the black and white items?

68
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:00,560
I'd like to hear the details.

69
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:03,200
Pig bristles.

70
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:04,490
Pig bristles

71
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:07,080
are about 3,000 yuan a box at the origin.

72
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:09,240
But when transported to Shanghai,

73
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,570
it becomes 50,000 yuan.

74
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,860
If it can be shipped to the United States,

75
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,400
600,000 yuan a box

76
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:15,770
might not be enough.

77
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,460
Of course I've heard of pig bristles.

78
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:21,010
They are in high demand all over the world.

79
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:24,640
But the best origin of pig bristles is Sichuan.

80
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,160
Secondly, Hunan,

81
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:28,480
is also in the KMT-controlled area.

82
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,720
Anyway, Mr. He has

83
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,280
plenty of top-quality bristles in his hands.

84
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,560
Hundreds of boxes.

85
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,450
Brother Jin,

86
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,080
don't you think this is

87
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,620
a lucrative business?

88
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,760
A business with a 200-fold profit,

89
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,090
how could it not be good?

90
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,120
Mr. He,

91
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,600
it seems you are indeed a hero.

92
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,560
You flatter me.

93
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:55,159
I must properly toast the two of you.

94
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:59,440
And also toast Changgeng and Huiru.

95
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,160
Cheers.

96
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:01,960
Cheers.

97
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,160
Together.

98
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,080
Cheers, Deputy Chief Jin.

99
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:16,280
Good wine.

100
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:17,680
Cheers, Madam.

101
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,160
Huiru,

102
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:22,520
About the conflict between Changgeng and Minister Zhou,

103
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:25,520
I have been trying my best to mediate.

104
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,920
I wonder if Changgeng can do me a favor

105
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:32,000
and not be so tough in the future?

106
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,360
Actually, I'm not that tough.

107
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,600
I shouldn't talk about people behind their backs,

108
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,490
but we are all friends here.

109
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,840
I feel that

110
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,370
Minister Zhou is not generous enough.

111
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,600
He should either

112
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,960
be more generous with money,

113
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,120
or

114
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,000
be more generous with positions.

115
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:52,800
Right?

116
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,640
Brother Jin,

117
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,290
I am different from you.

118
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,920
I think the current political situation,

119
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,720
and its tone,

120
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,200
are all about deceiving the common people.

121
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:05,960
My logic is,

122
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,960
if you want to achieve great things,

123
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:09,720
you must have money.

124
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,360
The premise of having money

125
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,680
is that you must have strength.

126
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,580
What do you say?

127
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:18,720
Ruisheng,

128
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:21,080
in front of Mr. and Mrs. Wang,

129
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,960
you have to say a fair word for Changgeng.

130
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:26,440
When Mr. Wang organized and established the government,

131
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,720
Changgeng brought his own

132
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,560
men, money, and guns to join.

133
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,700
He risked his life and followed them.

134
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:34,320
It wasn't easy to establish the Ministry of Police Affairs,

135
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,520
but someone else was made the minister.

136
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,400
Changgeng did all the work,

137
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,400
but someone else took the credit.

138
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,760
Do you think it's fair?

139
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:43,620
I also know that

140
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:44,840
now,

141
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:48,440
Mr. and Mrs. Wang look down on us,

142
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:49,700
thinking we are

143
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,440
too bloody.

144
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,330
Why are you saying this?

145
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,760
I'm telling the truth.

146
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,560
If we weren't bloody,

147
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,600
could this government be set up?

148
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,450
What about everyone's safety?

149
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,040
Don't you all know?

150
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:06,920
Mr. Shao was killed a few days ago.

151
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,320
What a pity.

152
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,600
Speaking of Mr. Shao, it reminds me.

153
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,520
The last time we ate here,

154
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:22,120
Mr. Shao sat in this seat of mine.

155
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,920
Speaking of him, I really...

156
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:28,290
Think back to when we came to Shanghai,

157
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,840
it was really thanks to Mr. Shao's guidance.

158
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,890
But later, this Mr. Shao...

159
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,640
Exactly.

160
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:35,820
He despised my status,

161
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,520
so we drifted apart.

162
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,280
Then,

163
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:43,010
I was targeted by the Chongqing elements.

164
00:08:43,159 --> 00:08:44,200
What a pity.

165
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,960
What's there to pity?

166
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,040
It's all fate.

167
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,320
Right?

168
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,320
Changgeng.

169
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,720
What Huiru said makes perfect sense

170
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,620
and is very practical.

171
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,400
I, Qiwu, never take sides.

172
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,960
I'm nobody's man.

173
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,960
I act only on fairness and conscience.

174
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,400
But please rest assured, Huiru.

175
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,800
I will definitely find the right time

176
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:12,800
to tell Mr. Wang about Changgeng's painstaking efforts

177
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,260
and selfless dedication,

178
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,760
and let him

179
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,800
decide for himself

180
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:20,240
the candidate for the Minister of Police Affairs.

181
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,360
If I fail to do so,

182
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,320
I'll quit being the Deputy Chief of Publicity.

183
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,400
I'll report to the Secret Service Headquarters

184
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,130
and be Changgeng's secretary.

185
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,240
Let's not talk about this.

186
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,240
Are you kidding?

187
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,360
You are the pen,

188
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,920
and he is the sword.

189
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:36,120
You two must unite.

190
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,760
Only then will people listen

191
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,890
to Mr. Wang's words.

192
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,720
Right?

193
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:40,880
Okay.

194
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,000
We will listen to Huiru.

195
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,720
We do what we say.

196
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:47,040
Come, let's raise our glasses

197
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:48,450
to toast Changgeng.

198
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,040
Together.

199
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,200
Come on.

200
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,560
Mr. He.

201
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,240
You look familiar to me.

202
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:02,400
Have we met somewhere before?

203
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,240
Deputy Chief Jin,

204
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,280
we have indeed met,

205
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,000
right here.

206
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,360
Here?

207
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:17,520
I remember

208
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,920
when I first met you,

209
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,200
you were in this exact seat,

210
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,920
singing and beating the rhythm.

211
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:30,440
♪ My hair bristles with anger ♪

212
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:36,200
By the railing.

213
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,840
Baozi.

214
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,440
I wonder if Deputy Chief Jin still remembers

215
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,840
the Meng Family Banquet.

216
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,240
I remember Deputy Chief Jin was sitting

217
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,560
in my wife's seat,

218
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:49,040
and speaking to Mr. Brown sitting here,

219
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,610
telling him about the Four Sprouts of Virtue.

220
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,120
A sense of compassion,

221
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,360
a sense of shame,

222
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:55,600
a sense of modesty and courtesy,

223
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,200
and a sense of right and wrong,

224
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:00,800
corresponding to benevolence, righteousness, propriety, and wisdom.

225
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,320
Deputy Chief Jin is truly profoundly learned.

226
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,120
I was deeply inspired.

227
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,640
Not at all.

228
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:07,800
Mr. He.

229
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,840
You are the one hiding your light under a bushel.

230
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,920
No.

231
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,080
Did you two know each other before, or

232
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,920
how did you get connected?

233
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:22,840
He,

234
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,740
how do you think I should reply to Mr. Jin?

235
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,080
Deputy Chief Jin.

236
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:32,480
You are now Chairman Wang's trusted writer.

237
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,440
A great contemporary literary figure.

238
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,960
I believe you can naturally understand

239
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:38,240
this profound and subtle fate

240
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:41,840
between Changgeng and me.

241
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,380
Right, Changgeng?

242
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:48,440
Mrs. He also looks familiar to me.

243
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,960
I also stayed at the Tian Mansion for a long time.

244
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,920
I was Mr. Tian's Scholar at that time.

245
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,440
Our Mrs. He

246
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,200
is an outstanding graduate of Great China University.

247
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,520
Mr. He's business

248
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,140
is all managed by his wife.

249
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:04,730
It seems that today,

250
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,290
everyone here is an expert.

251
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:13,800
'So subtle, it is formless.

252
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:20,200
So divine, it is soundless.'

253
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:22,980
Excellent.

254
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:25,720
Truly excellent.

255
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,620
Deputy Chief Jin flatters me.

256
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,400
I am no expert.

257
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:33,620
The real experts are Director Lin and Deputy Chief Jin.

258
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,920
I am just a businessman.

259
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,040
Here,

260
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,320
I mainly rely on Director Lin's guidance.

261
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,160
Over there,

262
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,560
I mainly rely on Mr. Dai's care.

263
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,440
Of course,

264
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:44,820
whatever business

265
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,200
you bosses want to do,

266
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,360
Jianghu Trading Company

267
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:49,840
will do it.

268
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,580
Not just bristles.

269
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:54,160
Gauze, Quinine,

270
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,720
and Tung oil, we...

271
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,240
Don't talk nonsense.

272
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,760
How could we get Tung oil?

273
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,900
We can't do Tung oil business now.

274
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,560
Chongqing borrowed money from the US.

275
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:06,020
The US specified Tung oil to pay off the debt.

276
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,980
No one dares to touch Tung oil now.

277
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,440
Not even Mr. Dai.

278
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:10,600
Right.

279
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,960
My wife's brain works better than mine.

280
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:15,440
It seems we are all old friends today.

281
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:17,520
I still say the same thing.

282
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:19,760
Let's make money together.

283
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,640
If we can catch big fish by the river,

284
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,360
why go to the middle of the river

